timeline.bodyText:
This is probably a misuse of the peek API and it makes it more complex to see what's going on here (it looks like a single operation but actually it's two).
I'd just use:
event.getDeposits().stream()
  .map(DepositUtil::convertDepositEventToOperationDeposit)
  .forEach(deposit -> {
    depositNavigableMap.put(deposit.getIndex(), deposit);
    depositMerkleTree.add(deposit.getData().hash_tree_root());
  });

For the record, the only time you need to use forEachOrdered rather than forEach is when you've moved to a parallel stream somewhere.  It doesn't hurt because a sequential stream just implements forEachOrdered as forEach but it makes me stop and go looking for the parallel call every time I see forEachOrdered.

